.TH SMFC\-CLIENT 1 smfc\-6.0.0
.SH NAME
.B smfc\-client
\- print a one\-shot snapshot of smfc\-managed fans and temperatures.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smfc\-client
[options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B smfc\-client
is a read\-only diagnostic tool that prints the current state of all fan controllers managed by
.BR smfc (1).
.PP
When the
.B [Exporter]
section is enabled in the configuration file and the smfc service is reachable, the snapshot is
fetched from the service's
.I /snapshot
HTTP endpoint (online mode).
On any failure \(en connection refused, timeout, or malformed response \(en the tool falls back
transparently to the standalone mode, which reads sensors directly through
.BR ipmitool (1)
and
.BR smartctl (8).
.PP
The output is structured in sections:
.IP \(bu 2
.B Banner
\(en program name, version, config path, and data source.
.IP \(bu 2
.B BMC
\(en product name and current IPMI fan mode
(with
.BR \-V :
manufacturer, firmware revision, IPMI version, and platform class).
.IP \(bu 2
.B Fan controllers
\(en a summary table with one row per enabled controller: section name, type, IPMI zone(s),
device count, aggregated temperature, and current fan level.
.IP \(bu 2
.B Per\-controller blocks
(with
.B \-V
only) \(en one block per non\-CONST controller with the steering window, optional control\-function
curve, current temperature and level, optional HD standby guard summary, and a per\-device
temperature list.
.IP \(bu 2
.B IPMI zones
\(en live fan level per zone.
.PP
Temperature and level cells are colour\-coded when the output is a terminal (suppressed with
.BR \-nc ):
.BR DIM " (below floor), " GREEN " (working in range), " YELLOW " (upper 30% of window), " RED " (at or above ceiling)."
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show a help message and exit.
.TP
.BI \-c " FILE" ", \-\-config " FILE
Configuration file (default:
.IR /etc/smfc/smfc.conf ).
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-sudo
Run
.BR ipmitool (1)
and
.BR smartctl (8)
under
.BR sudo (8).
Required when the invoking user lacks direct BMC or disk access.
.TP
.B \-nc, \-\-no\-color
Disable ANSI color output even when stdout is a terminal.
.TP
.B \-V, \-\-verbose
Show extended output: additional BMC fields, per\-controller blocks with per\-device temperature
rows, HD standby guard state, and service uptime (online mode only).
.TP
.B \-sa, \-\-standalone
Bypass the smfc service and read sensors directly via
.BR ipmitool (1)
and
.BR smartctl (8),
even when the service is reachable.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Show the program version and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/smfc/smfc.conf
Default configuration file.
.TP
.I /etc/default/smfc
Environment file for the smfc systemd unit.
.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/smfc.service
systemd service unit for smfc.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Successful exit.
.TP
.B 6
Configuration file error (missing, unreadable, or invalid).
.TP
.B 8
IPMI initialization error (ipmitool not found or BMC not accessible).
.TP
.B 9
udev initialization error.
.SH NOTES
The standalone mode contacts the BMC directly and may require root privileges or
.BR sudo (8)
(\c
.BR \-s ).
.PP
The IPMI BMC initialization timeout in standalone mode is 5 seconds (shorter than the 120 seconds
used by the smfc service), so the tool returns quickly when the BMC is unreachable.
.PP
CONST controllers (fixed fan level, no temperature source) are shown in the Fan controllers table
but are excluded from the per\-controller verbose blocks.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR smfc (1),
.BR ipmitool (1),
.BR smartctl (8),
.BR systemctl (1)
